heading_17 = heading_15 + ">>37. Overview"
heading_18 = heading_17 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_18, 'This Chapter contains a set of standard provisions (sections 39, 40 and 41) that set out certain circumstances in which directors and other officers of a body corporate can incur criminal liability as a result of an offence by the body corporate.')
heading_19 = heading_17 + ">>(2) Only one of sections 39, 40 and 41 can apply to an offence."
CONTEXT(heading_19, '[Section 37 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_18 = heading_15 + ">>38. Term used officer; In this Chapter "
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>officer, in relation to a body corporate, has the meaning given in the  Corporations Act 2001  (Commonwealth) section 9."
CONTEXT(heading_19, '[Section 38 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_19 = heading_15 + ">>39. Officer liability for corporate offence onus on prosecution to prove reasonable steps not taken"
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'This section applies to an offence if a provision of this Code, or of another written law, expressly provides that it applies to the offence.')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'If a body corporate is guilty of an offence to which this section applies, an officer of the body corporate is also guilty of the offence if the officer failed to take all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_22 = heading_19 + ">>(3) In determining whether things done or omitted to be done by the officer constitute reasonable steps, a court must have regard to "
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'what the officer knew, or ought to have known, about the commission of the offence by the body corporate and')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'whether the officer was in a position to influence the conduct of the body corporate in relation to the commission of the offence and')
heading_25 = heading_22 + ">>(c) any other relevant matter."
CONTEXT(heading_25, '[Section 39 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_20 = heading_15 + ">>40. Officer liability for corporate offence onus on prosecution to prove reasonable steps not taken if evidence suggesting reasonable steps adduced"
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'This section applies to an offence if a provision of this Code, or of another written law, expressly provides that it applies to the offence.')
heading_22 = heading_20 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'If a body corporate is guilty of an offence to which this section applies, an officer of the body corporate is also guilty of the offence unless the officer took all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_23 = heading_20 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'The prosecutor has the onus of proving that the officer failed to take all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate if, and only if, evidence that suggests a reasonable possibility that the officer took all reasonable steps is first adduced by or on behalf of the officer.')
heading_24 = heading_20 + ">>(4) In determining whether things done or omitted to be done by the officer constitute reasonable steps, a court must have regard to "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'what the officer knew, or ought to have known, about the commission of the offence by the body corporate and')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'whether the officer was in a position to influence the conduct of the body corporate in relation to the commission of the offence and')
heading_27 = heading_24 + ">>(c) any other relevant matter."
CONTEXT(heading_27, '[Section 40 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_21 = heading_15 + ">>41. Officer liability for corporate offence onus on officer to prove reasonable steps taken"
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'This section applies to an offence if a provision of this Code, or of another written law, expressly provides that it applies to the offence.')
heading_23 = heading_21 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'If a body corporate is guilty of an offence to which this section applies, an officer of the body corporate is also guilty of the offence unless the officer took all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_24 = heading_21 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'The officer has the onus of proving that the officer took all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_25 = heading_21 + ">>(4) In determining whether things done or omitted to be done by the officer constitute reasonable steps, a court must have regard to "
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'what the officer knew, or ought to have known, about the commission of the offence by the body corporate and')
heading_27 = heading_25 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'whether the officer was in a position to influence the conduct of the body corporate in relation to the commission of the offence and')
heading_28 = heading_25 + ">>(c) any other relevant matter."
CONTEXT(heading_28, '[Section 41 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_22 = heading_15 + ">>42. Further provisions relating to criminal liability of officers of bodies corporate"
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'This Chapter does not affect the liability of a body corporate for any offence.')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'This Chapter does not affect the liability of an officer, or any other person, under Chapters II, LVII, LVIII and LIX.')
heading_25 = heading_22 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'An officer of a body corporate may be charged with, and convicted of, an offence in accordance with section 39, 40 or 41 whether or not the body corporate is charged with, or convicted of, the offence committed by the body corporate.')
heading_26 = heading_22 + ">>(4) If an officer of a body corporate who is charged with an offence in accordance with section 39, 40 or 41 claims that the body"
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'the onus of proving the defence is on the officer and')
heading_28 = heading_26 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'the standard of proof required is the standard that would apply to the body corporate in relation to the defence.')
heading_27 = heading_22 + ">>(5) Subsection (4) does not limit any other defence available to the officer."
CONTEXT(heading_27, '[Section 42 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_23 = heading_15 + ">>43. Penalties"
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>(1) This section applies to an offence if "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'section 39, 40 or 41 applies to the offence and')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'the specified penalty for the offence applies only to a body corporate.')
heading_25 = heading_23 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'The maximum penalty for the offence if committed by an officer of a body corporate is one-fifth of the maximum penalty that could be imposed on the body corporate.')
heading_26 = heading_23 + ">>(3) This section does not limit the; Sentencing Act 1995 .; [Section 43 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]; Part II  Offences against public order [Chapter VI (s. 37-43) deleted No. 70 of 1988 s. 8(1).]"
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'Chapter VII  Sedition')
heading_24 = heading_15 + ">>44. Term used seditious intention; An intention to effect any of the following purposes, that is to say "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'To bring the Sovereign into hatred or contempt')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'To excite disaffection against the Sovereign, or the Government or Constitution of the United Kingdom, or of the Commonwealth of Australia, or of Western Australia as by law established, or against either House of Parliament of the United Kingdom, of the Commonwealth of Australia, or of Western Australia, or against the administration of justice')
heading_27 = heading_24 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'To excite Her Majestys subjects to attempt to procure the alteration of any matter in the State as by law established otherwise than by lawful means')
heading_28 = heading_24 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'To raise discontent or disaffection amongst Her Majestys subjects')
heading_29 = heading_24 + ">>(e) To promote feelings of ill-will and enmity between different classes of Her Majestys subjects"
heading_30 = heading_29 + ">>is a seditious intention, unless it is justified by section 45."
CONTEXT(heading_30, '[Section 44 amended No. 44 of 2009 s. 11.]')
heading_25 = heading_15 + ">>45. Acts excepted from s. 44; It is lawful for any person "
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'To endeavour in good faith to show that the Sovereign has been mistaken in any of Her counsels or')
heading_27 = heading_25 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'To point out in good faith errors or defects in the Government or Constitution of the United Kingdom, or of the Commonwealth of Australia, or of Western Australia as by law established, or in legislation, or in the administration of justice, with a view to the reformation of such errors or defects or')
heading_28 = heading_25 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'To excite in good faith Her Majestys subjects to attempt to procure by lawful means the alteration of any matter in the State as by law established or')
heading_29 = heading_25 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'To point out in good faith in order to their removal any matters which are producing or have a tendency to produce feelings of ill-will and enmity between different classes of Her Majestys subjects.')
heading_26 = heading_15 + ">>46. Terms used seditious enterprise, seditious words, seditious writing"
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'A seditious enterprise is an enterprise which is undertaken in order to the carrying out of a seditious intention.')
heading_28 = heading_26 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'Seditious words are words expressive of a seditious intention.')
heading_29 = heading_26 + ">>content3"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'The term seditious writing includes anything intended to be read, and any sign or visible representation, which is expressive of a seditious intention.')
heading_27 = heading_15 + ">>47. Oath to kill person; Any person who "
heading_28 = heading_27 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'Administers or is present at and consents to the administering of, any oath, or engagement in the nature of an oath, purporting to bind the person who takes it to kill any person or')
heading_29 = heading_27 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'Takes any such oath or engagement, not being compelled to do so or')
heading_30 = heading_27 + ">>(3) Attempts to induce any person to take any such oath or engagement"
heading_31 = heading_30 + ">>is guilty of a crime, and is liable to imprisonment for 20 years."
CONTEXT(heading_31, '[Section 47 amended No. 118 of 1981 s. 4 No. 52 of 1984 s. 10 No. 51 of 1992 s. 16(2) No. 29 of 2008 s. 16(1).]')
heading_28 = heading_15 + ">>48. Other unlawful oaths; Any person who "
heading_29 = heading_28 + ">>(1) Administers, or is present at and consents to the administering of, any oath or engagement in the nature of an oath purporting to bind the person who takes it to act in any of the ways following, that is to say "
heading_30 = heading_29 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_30, 'To engage in any seditious enterprise')
heading_31 = heading_29 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_31, 'To commit any indictable offence other than one entailing the killing of a person')
heading_32 = heading_29 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_32, 'To disturb the public peace')
heading_33 = heading_29 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_33, 'To be of any association, society, or confederacy formed for the purpose of doing any such act as aforesaid')
heading_34 = heading_29 + ">>e"
CONTEXT(heading_34, 'To obey the orders or commands of any committee or body of men not lawfully constituted, or of any leader or commander or other person not having authority by law for that purpose')
heading_35 = heading_29 + ">>f"
CONTEXT(heading_35, 'Not to inform or give evidence against any associate, confederate, or other person')
heading_36 = heading_29 + ">>g"
CONTEXT(heading_36, 'Not to reveal or discover any unlawful association, society, or confederacy, or any illegal act done or to be done, or any illegal oath or engagement that may have been administered or tendered to or taken by himself or any other')
heading_30 = heading_28 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_30, 'Takes any such oath or engagement, not being compelled to do so or')
heading_31 = heading_28 + ">>(3) Attempts to induce any person to take any such oath or engagement"
heading_32 = heading_31 + ">>is guilty of a crime, and is liable to imprisonment for 7 years."
CONTEXT(heading_32, '[Section 48 amended No. 52 of 1984 s. 11 No. 70 of 1988 s. 8(2) No. 51 of 1992 s. 16(2) No. 29 of 2008 s. 16(2).]')
heading_29 = heading_15 + ">>49. Compulsion, how far a defence to s. 47 and 48; A person who takes any such oath or engagement as is mentioned in sections 47 and 48 cannot set up as a defence that he was compelled to do so, unless within 14 days after taking it, or, if he is prevented by actual force or sickness, within 14 days after the termination of such prevention, he declares by information on oath before some member of the Executive Council or justice of the peace, or, if he is on actual service in Her Majestys forces by sea or land, either by such information or by information to his commanding officer, the whole of what he knows concerning the matter, including the person or persons by whom and in whose presence, and the place where, and the time when, the oath or engagement was administered or taken.; [Section 49 amended No. 44 of 2009 s. 12.] ["
