heading_42 = heading_40 + ">>[Section 221BF inserted No. 4 of 2019 s. 4.]; Chapter XXVIA  Facilitating activities of criminal organisations  [Heading inserted No. 49 of 2012 s. 173(3).]"
heading_43 = heading_42 + ">>221C. Terms used"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>(1) In this Chapter ; COC Act means the  Criminal Organisations Control Act 2012"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'criminal organisation has the meaning given in section 221D')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'declared criminal organisation has the meaning given in the  Criminal Organisations Control Act 2012 section 3(1)')
heading_47 = heading_44 + ">>content3"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'indictable offence includes conduct engaged in outside this State (including outside Australia) that, if it occurred in this State, would constitute an indictable offence.')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'A term used in this Chapter and also in the COC Act has the same meaning in this Chapter as it has in that Act, unless the term is defined in this Code or the context requires otherwise.')
heading_43 = heading_40 + ">>[Section 221C inserted No. 49 of 2012 s. 173(3).]"
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>221D. Term used criminal organisation"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>(1) For the purposes of this Chapter, an entity is a criminal organisation if "
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'the entity is a declared criminal organisation or')
heading_47 = heading_45 + ">>(b) all of the following apply to the entity "
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>(i) the entity is an organisation"
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_49, '(ii) members of the organisation associate for the purpose of organising, planning, facilitating, supporting or engaging in serious criminal activity')
heading_50 = heading_48 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_50, '(iii) the organisation represents a risk to public safety and order in this State.')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>(2) In determining whether an entity is a criminal organisation for the purposes of subsection (1)(b) "
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'a court may have regard to any of the matters that a designated authority is entitled to have regard to under the COC Act section 13(2) (other than paragraph (e)) in considering whether or not to make a declaration under that Act and')
heading_48 = heading_46 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'section 13(3) of that Act applies with all necessary changes for the purposes of the court satisfying itself that subsection (1)(b)(ii) of this section applies to the entity.')
heading_44 = heading_40 + ">>[Section 221D inserted No. 49 of 2012 s. 173(3).]"
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>221E. Participating in activities of criminal organisation"
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'A person who, for the purpose of enhancing the ability of a criminal organisation to facilitate or commit an indictable offence, by act or omission, participates in or contributes to any activity of the criminal organisation is guilty of a crime, and is liable to imprisonment for 5 years.')
heading_41 = heading_15 + ">>Summary conviction penalty imprisonment for 2 years."
heading_42 = heading_41 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'For the purposes of subsection (1), facilitation of an offence does not require knowledge of a particular offence the commission of which is facilitated, or that an offence actually be committed.')
heading_43 = heading_41 + ">>(3) In a prosecution for an offence under subsection (1), it is not necessary to prove that "
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'the criminal organisation actually facilitated or committed an indictable offence or')
heading_45 = heading_43 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'the participation or contribution of the accused actually enhanced the ability of the criminal organisation to facilitate or commit an indictable offence or')
heading_46 = heading_43 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'the accused knew the specific nature of any indictable offence that may have been facilitated or committed by the criminal organisation or')
heading_47 = heading_43 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'the accused knew the identity of any of the persons who are members of the criminal organisation.')
heading_44 = heading_41 + ">>(4) In determining whether an accused participates in or contributes to any activity of a criminal organisation, the court may consider, among other factors, whether the accused "
heading_45 = heading_44 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_45, 'uses a name, word, symbol or other representation that identifies, or is associated with, the criminal organisation or')
heading_46 = heading_44 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'frequently associates with members of the criminal organisation or')
heading_47 = heading_44 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'receives any benefit from the criminal organisation or')
heading_48 = heading_44 + ">>(d) repeatedly engages in activities at the instruction of any of the members of the criminal organisation."
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>[Section 221E inserted No. 49 of 2012 s. 173(3).]"
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>221F. Instructing commission of offence for benefit of criminal organisation"
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_51, 'A person who is a member of a criminal organisation and who instructs, directly or indirectly, any person to commit an offence under this Code or any other written law, or an offence against a law of a jurisdiction other than Western Australia, for the benefit of, at the direction of, or in association with, the criminal organisation is guilty of a crime, and is liable to imprisonment for 20 years.')
heading_52 = heading_50 + ">>(2) In a prosecution for an offence under subsection (1), it is not necessary to prove that "
heading_53 = heading_52 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'an offence other than the offence under subsection (1) was actually committed or')
heading_54 = heading_52 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'the accused instructed a particular person to commit an offence or')
heading_55 = heading_52 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_55, 'the accused knew the identity of all of the persons who are members of the criminal organisation.')
heading_50 = heading_48 + ">>[Section 221F inserted No. 49 of 2012 s. 173(3).]; Part V  Offences against the person and relating to parental rights and duties and against the reputation of individuals  [Heading amended No. 5 of 2008 s. 129(2).]; Chapter XXVI  Assaults and violence to the person generally Justification, excuse and circumstances of aggravation  [Heading amended No. 38 of 2004 s. 63.]"
heading_51 = heading_50 + ">>221. Term used circumstances of aggravation"
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>(1) In this Part ; circumstances of aggravation means circumstances in which "
heading_53 = heading_52 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'the offender is in a family relationship with the victim of the offence, other than where subsection (1A) applies or')
heading_54 = heading_52 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_54, 'a child was present when the offence was committed, other than where subsection (1A) applies or')
heading_55 = heading_52 + ">>(c) the conduct of the offender in committing the offence constituted a breach of an order, other than an order under Part 1C, made or registered under the"
heading_56 = heading_55 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_56, 'Restraining Orders Act 1997 or to which that Act applies or')
heading_56 = heading_52 + ">>(d) the victim is of or over the age of 60 years.  (1A) This subsection applies if "
heading_57 = heading_56 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_57, 'the offender was a child at the time of the commission of the relevant offence and')
heading_58 = heading_56 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_58, 'the only circumstance of aggravation is the offender was in a family relationship with the victim at the time of the commission of the offence, or a child was present at the time of the commission of the offence, or both.')
heading_53 = heading_51 + ">>(2) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_53, 'family relationship has the meaning given in the  Restraining Orders Act 1997 section 4(1).')
heading_51 = heading_48 + ">>[Section 221 inserted No. 38 of 2004 s. 64 amended No. 49 of 2016 s. 99 No. 30 of 2020 s. 4.]"
heading_52 = heading_51 + ">>222"
CONTEXT(heading_52, 'Term used assault')
heading_42 = heading_15 + ">>content27"
CONTEXT(heading_42, 'A person who strikes, touches, or moves, or otherwise applies force of any kind to the person of another, either directly or indirectly, without his consent, or with his consent if the consent is obtained by fraud, or who by any bodily act or gesture attempts or threatens to apply force of any kind to the person of another without his consent, under such circumstances that the person making the attempt or threat has actually or apparently a present ability to effect his purpose, is said to assault that other person, and the act is called an assault.')
heading_43 = heading_15 + ">>The term applies force includes the case of applying heat, light, electrical force, gas, odour, or any other substance or thing whatever if applied in such a degree as to cause injury or personal discomfort."
heading_44 = heading_43 + ">>223"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'Assault is unlawful')
heading_44 = heading_15 + ">>content29"
CONTEXT(heading_44, 'An assault is unlawful and constitutes an offence unless it is authorised or justified or excused by law.')
heading_45 = heading_15 + ">>The application of force by one person to the person of another may be unlawful, although it is done with the consent of that other person."
heading_46 = heading_45 + ">>224"
CONTEXT(heading_46, 'Execution of sentence is lawful')
heading_46 = heading_15 + ">>It is lawful for a person who is charged by law with the duty of executing or giving effect to the lawful sentence of a court to execute or give effect to that sentence."
heading_47 = heading_46 + ">>225"
CONTEXT(heading_47, 'Execution of process is lawful')
heading_47 = heading_15 + ">>It is lawful for a person who is charged by law with the duty of executing the lawful process of a court, and who is required to arrest or detain another person under such process, and for every person lawfully assisting a person so charged, to arrest or detain that other person according to the terms of the process."
heading_48 = heading_47 + ">>226"
CONTEXT(heading_48, 'Execution of warrant is lawful')
heading_48 = heading_15 + ">>It is lawful for a person who is charged by law with the duty of executing a lawful warrant issued by any court or justice or other person having jurisdiction to issue it, and who is required to arrest or detain another person under such warrant, and for every person lawfully assisting a person so charged, to arrest or detain that other person according to the directions of the warrant."
heading_49 = heading_48 + ">>227"
CONTEXT(heading_49, 'Sentence, process or warrant issued without authority, effect of')
heading_49 = heading_15 + ">>If the sentence was passed, or the process was issued, by a court having jurisdiction under any circumstances to pass such a sentence, or to issue such process, or if the warrant was issued by a court or justice or other person having authority under any circumstances to issue such a warrant, it is immaterial whether the court or justice or person had or had not authority to pass the sentence or issue the process or warrant in the particular case unless the person executing the same knows that the sentence or process or warrant was in fact passed or issued without authority."
heading_50 = heading_49 + ">>228"
CONTEXT(heading_50, 'Sentence, process or warrant issued without authority, liability of person executing etc.')
heading_15 = heading_3 + ">>A person who executes or assists in executing any sentence, process, or warrant which purports to be passed or issued by a court, justice, or other person, and who would be justified, under section 224, 225, 226 or 227, in executing the same if it had  [Section 228 amended No. 44 of 2009 s. 13.]"
heading_16 = heading_15 + ">>229. Arrest of wrong person"
heading_17 = heading_16 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_17, 'A person who, being duly authorised to execute a warrant to arrest one person, arrests another person, believing in good faith and on reasonable grounds that the person arrested is the person named in the warrant, is not criminally responsible for doing so to any greater extent than if the person arrested had been the person named in the warrant.')
heading_18 = heading_16 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_18, 'Any person who lawfully assists in making such an arrest, believing that the person arrested is the person named in the warrant, or who, being required by the warrant to receive and detain the person named in it, receives and detains the person so arrested, is not criminally responsible for doing so to any greater extent than if the person arrested had been the person named in the warrant.')
heading_17 = heading_15 + ">>230. Process or warrant that is bad in law, liability of person executing etc."
CONTEXT(heading_17, 'When any process or warrant is bad in law by reason of some defect in substance or in form apparent on the face of it, a person who, in good faith and believing that it is good in law, acts in the execution of the process or warrant, is not criminally responsible for anything done in such execution to any greater extent than if the process or warrant were good in law.')
heading_18 = heading_15 + ">>231. Executing sentence, process or warrant or making arrest, using force for"
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_19, 'It is lawful for a person who is engaged in the lawful execution of any sentence, process, or warrant, or in making any arrest, and for any person lawfully assisting him, to use such force as may be reasonably necessary to overcome any force used in resisting such execution or arrest.')
heading_20 = heading_18 + ">>(2) In determining whether any process or warrant might have been executed, or any arrest made, in a less forcible manner, the following shall be taken into account "
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'whether the person executing the process or warrant had it with him or her and produced it at the time')
heading_22 = heading_20 + ">>(b) if it was practicable to do so at the time, whether the person making an arrest, whether with or without a warrant, gave notice of the process or warrant under which the person was acting or of the cause of the arrest.; [Section 231 amended No. 59 of 2006 s. 20.] ["
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>232."
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'Deleted No. 59 of 2006 s. 21.]')
heading_19 = heading_15 + ">>233. Flight from arrest, use of force to prevent"
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'When any person is proceeding lawfully to arrest, with or without warrant, another person, and the person sought to be arrested takes to flight, or appears to be about to take to flight, in order to avoid arrest, it is lawful for the person seeking to make the arrest, and for any person lawfully assisting that person, to use such force as may be reasonably necessary to prevent the escape of the person sought to be arrested.')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>(2) Subsection (1) does not authorise the use of force that is intended or is likely to cause death or grievous bodily harm unless "
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'the person who uses that force is a police officer or a person assisting a police officer and')
heading_23 = heading_21 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'the person sought to be arrested is reasonably suspected of having committed an offence punishable with imprisonment for life and')
heading_24 = heading_21 + ">>(c) the person sought to be arrested is called on to surrender before that force is used.; [Section 233 inserted No. 119 of 1985 s. 6.] ["
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>234."
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'Deleted No. 119 of 1985 s. 7.]')
heading_20 = heading_15 + ">>235. Escape or rescue after arrest, use of force to prevent"
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'When any person has lawfully arrested another person for any offence, it is lawful for him to use such force as may be reasonably necessary to prevent the escape or rescue of the person arrested.')
heading_22 = heading_20 + ">>(2) Subsection (1) does not authorise the use of force that is intended or is likely to cause death or grievous bodily harm unless the offence referred to in that subsection is punishable with imprisonment for 14 years or upwards, with or without any other punishment.; [Section 235 inserted No. 119 of 1985 s. 8.] [ 236, 237.; Deleted No. 59 of 2006 s. 22.]"
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>238. Riot, use of force to suppress"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'It is lawful for any person to use such force as is necessary to suppress a riot, and is reasonably proportioned to the danger to be apprehended from its continuance.')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>239. Riot, use of force to suppress by justice and police officer"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'It is lawful for a justice to use or order to be used, and for a police officer to use, such force as he believes, on reasonable grounds, to be necessary in order to suppress a riot, and as is reasonably proportioned to the danger which he believes, on reasonable grounds, is to be apprehended from its continuance.')
heading_25 = heading_22 + ">>240. Riot, use of force to suppress by person acting under lawful order"
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'It is lawful for any person acting in good faith in obedience to orders, not manifestly unlawful, given by a justice for the suppression of a riot, to use such force as he believes, on reasonable grounds, to be necessary for carrying such orders into effect.')
heading_27 = heading_25 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'Whether any particular order so given is or is not manifestly unlawful is a question of law.')
heading_26 = heading_22 + ">>241. Riot, use of force to suppress by person acting without order in case of emergency"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'When any person, whether subject to military law or not, believes, on reasonable grounds, that serious mischief will arise from a riot before there is time to procure the intervention of a justice, it is lawful for him to use such force as he believes, on reasonable grounds, to be necessary for the suppression of the riot, and as is reasonably proportioned to the danger which he believes, on reasonable grounds, is to be apprehended from its continuance.')
heading_27 = heading_22 + ">>242. Riot, use of force to suppress by military personnel"
heading_28 = heading_27 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'It is lawful for a person who is bound by military law to obey the lawful commands of his superior officer to obey any command given him by his superior officer in order to the suppression of a riot, unless the command is manifestly unlawful.')
heading_29 = heading_27 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_29, 'Whether any particular command is or is not manifestly unlawful is a question of law.')
heading_28 = heading_22 + ">>243"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'Violence by mentally impaired person, use of force to prevent')
heading_16 = heading_3 + ">>It is lawful for any person to use such force as is reasonably necessary in order to prevent a person whom he believes, on  [Section 243 inserted No. 59 of 2006 s. 23.]"
heading_17 = heading_16 + ">>244. Home invasion, use of force to prevent etc."
heading_18 = heading_17 + ">>(1) It is lawful for a person (the occupant"
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>) who is in peaceable possession of a dwelling to use any force or do anything else that the occupant believes, on reasonable grounds, to be necessary "
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'to prevent a home invader from wrongfully entering the dwelling or an associated place or')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'to cause a home invader who is wrongfully in the dwelling or on or in an associated place to leave the dwelling or place or')
heading_22 = heading_19 + ">>(c) to make effectual defence against violence used or threatened in relation to a person by a home invader who is "
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>i"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'attempting to wrongfully enter the dwelling or an associated place or')
heading_20 = heading_18 + ">>(ii) wrongfully in the dwelling or on or in an associated place; or"
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>d"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'to prevent a home invader from committing, or make a home invader stop committing, an offence in the dwelling or on or in an associated place.  (1A) Despite subsection (1), it is not lawful for the occupant to use force that is intended, or that is likely, to cause death to a home invader unless the occupant believes, on reasonable grounds, that violence is being or is likely to be used or is threatened in relation to a person by a home invader.')
heading_19 = heading_17 + ">>(2) A person is a home invader for the purposes of subsection (1) if the occupant believes, on reasonable grounds, that the person "
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'intends to commit an offence or')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>(b) is committing or has committed an offence,"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'in the dwelling or on or in an associated place.')
heading_20 = heading_17 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'The authorisation conferred by subsection (1)(a), (b) or (d) extends to a person assisting the occupant or acting by the occupants authority.')
heading_21 = heading_17 + ">>(4)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'If under subsection (1)(c) it is lawful for the occupant to use a degree of force, it is lawful for another person acting in good faith in aid of the occupant to use the same degree of force to defend the occupant.')
heading_22 = heading_17 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'This section has effect even if the conduct it authorises would not otherwise be authorised under this Chapter.')
heading_23 = heading_17 + ">>(6) In this section "
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>associated place means "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'any place that is used exclusively in connection with, or for purposes ancillary to, the occupation of the dwelling and')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'if the dwelling is one of 2 or more dwellings in one building or group of buildings, a place that occupants of the dwellings use in common with one another')
heading_25 = heading_23 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'offence means an offence in addition to any wrongful entry')
heading_26 = heading_23 + ">>place means any land, building or structure, or a part of any land, building or structure."
CONTEXT(heading_26, '[Section 244 inserted No. 45 of 2000 s. 4 amended No. 29 of 2008 s. 7.]')
heading_18 = heading_16 + ">>245. Term used provocation"
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>content1"
CONTEXT(heading_19, 'The term provocation used with reference to an offence of which an assault is an element, means and includes, except as hereinafter stated, any wrongful act or insult of such a nature as to be likely, when done to an ordinary person, or in the presence of an ordinary person to another person who is under his  A lawful act is not provocation to any person for an assault.')
heading_20 = heading_18 + ">>content2"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'An act which a person does in consequence of incitement given by another person in order to induce him to do the act and thereby to furnish an excuse for committing an assault, is not provocation to that other person for an assault.')
heading_21 = heading_18 + ">>An arrest which is unlawful is not necessarily provocation for an assault, but it may be evidence of provocation to a person who knows of the illegality."
CONTEXT(heading_21, '[Section 245 amended No. 4 of 2004 s. 61(1).]')
heading_19 = heading_16 + ">>246. Defence of provocation"
CONTEXT(heading_19, 'A person is not criminally responsible for an assault committed upon a person who gives him provocation for the assault, if he is in fact deprived by the provocation of the power of self-control, and acts upon it on the sudden and before there is time for his passion to cool provided that the force used is not disproportionate to the provocation, and is not intended, and is not such as is likely to cause death or grievous bodily harm.')
heading_17 = heading_3 + ">>Whether any particular act or insult is such as to be likely to deprive an ordinary person of the power of self-control and to induce him to assault the person by whom the act or insult is done or offered, and whether, in any particular case, the person provoked was actually deprived by the provocation of the power"
heading_18 = heading_17 + ">>247. Repetition of insult, use of force to prevent"
CONTEXT(heading_18, 'It is lawful for any person to use such force as is reasonably necessary to prevent the repetition of an act or insult of such a nature as to be provocation to him for an assault provided that the force used is not intended, and is not such as is likely, to cause death or grievous bodily harm.')
heading_19 = heading_17 + ">>248. Self-defence"
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>(1) In this section "
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'harmful act means an act that is an element of an offence under this Part other than Chapter XXXV.')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'A harmful act done by a person is lawful if the act is done in self-defence under subsection (4).')
heading_22 = heading_19 + ">>(3) If "
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'a person unlawfully kills another person in circumstances which, but for this section, would constitute murder and')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>(b) the persons act that causes the other persons death would be an act done in self-defence under subsection (4) but for the fact that the act is not a reasonable response by the person in the circumstances as the person believes them to be,"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'the person is guilty of manslaughter and not murder.')
heading_23 = heading_19 + ">>(4) A persons harmful act is done in self-defence if "
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'the person believes the act is necessary to defend the person or another person from a harmful act, including a harmful act that is not imminent and')
heading_25 = heading_23 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'the persons harmful act is a reasonable response by the person in the circumstances as the person believes them to be and')
heading_26 = heading_23 + ">>c"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'there are reasonable grounds for those beliefs.')
heading_24 = heading_19 + ">>(5)"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'A persons harmful act is not done in self-defence if it is done to defend the person or another person from a harmful act that is lawful.')
